description: The exact origin somewhat unclear. Quite possibly from Old English, from a  reduplication of mash. Cognates include Saterland Frisian Miskmask and German Mischmasch.

entries.meaning: A collection containing a variety of miscellaneous things.

verbs.description: mishmash (third-person singular simple present mishmashes, present participle mishmashing, simple past and past participle mishmashed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To mix together, especially in a confused way.
